        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the green stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> off the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>and slice into 1.5cm thick rounds</p><p>Coat the <strong>aubergine rounds</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off the excess, then add to the <strong>beaten egg</strong> and finally press into the <strong>panko</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to evenly coat all over</p><p>Add the <strong>coated aubergine rounds</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined tray and put in the oven for 25-30 min or until crisp, golden and cooked through</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 2,
